nd</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">”, but we hope that the commen</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">ts below are useful in informing the Committee’s deliberations.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">1.4 </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">It is important to note that th</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">is submission is written in the context of </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">The Government response to the seventh report of the Scottish Affairs Committee session 2010-12 on The Crown </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">Estate in Scotland</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">,</span><a name="_ftnref2"></a><a href="#_ftn2">[2]</a><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> i</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">n </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">which</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> the UK Government rejected </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">recommendations</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> to devolve The Crown Estate </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">assets.</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">2. </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">About The Crown Estate in Scotland</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">2.1 </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">The Crown Estate is committed to Scotland. Our annual reports illustrate how we </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">work with stakeholders</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> and how we leverage expertise and investment from our UK-wide business to support key sectors in Scotland.</span><a name="_ftnref3"></a><a href="#_ftn3">[3]</a></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">2.2 </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Our remit is to maintain and enhance the value of </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">our </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">assets over the long-term while delivering a return to government, and to do so with due </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">regard to good management. This means that, in managing assets commercially, we consider how our investments and developments may deliver real benefits to communities, to Scotland and to the UK generally.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">2.3 </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">In fulfilling this role, our team in Scotland a</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">nd London work to enable and facilitate sustainable economic development.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">2.4 </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">In mature sectors</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> such as tourism and aquaculture, we invest in</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">, </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">and secure investment in</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">, </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">specific projects (e.g. marine leisure developments). We also work with industry, loca</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">l authorities and agencies such as Highlands &amp; Islands Enterprise (HIE), to ensure a coordinated and collaborative approach at local, regional and national level.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">2.5 </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">In emerging sectors such as offshore </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">renewables</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> and carbon capture &amp; storage (CCS), we co</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">ordinate a range of strategic activity designed to accelerate development and de-risk investment. We work closely with organisations such as Marine Scotland, Scottish Enterprise and local authorities, in addition to </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">developers and </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">energy companies, to help</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> establish this sector within the UK’s energy mix.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">2.6 </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">The Crown Estate’s </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">holdings in Scotland comprise:</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Almost all the</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> seabed out to the 12 nautical mile territorial limit</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">, and around half the foreshore</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">. The Crown Estate has the right to explore and </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">utilise the resources of the UK continental shelf (excluding oil, gas and coal), including the ri</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">ght to license renewable energy</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">43,000 hectares of rural land, including the </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Gl</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">enlivet</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">, </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Fochabers</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">, </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Applegirth</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">and </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Whitehill</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> estates. </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">We currently have </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">689 </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">tena</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">ncies which include </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">195</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> agricultural tenancies, </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">67</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> commercial tenancies and </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">102 </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">residential tenancies</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Retail property in Edinburgh</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">2.7 </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">In </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">2012/13</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> o</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">ur gross surplus in Scotland was £11.6 million</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">, four per cent of the</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> £283.2 million </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">total </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">for the UK as a wh</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">ole. </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">All net surplus is returned to the Treasury for public spending. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">2.8 </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Our </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">net investme</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">nt in Scotland in 2012/13 was</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> £4.4 million</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">, and from</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> 2010/11 to 2012/13 it totalled </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">£11.3 million.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">3. </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">The</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> land reform agenda</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">3.1 </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">While we acknowledge the </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">success of the community land ownership initiatives which have taken place in Scotland, </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">our experience indicates that many of the benefits that could accrue can also be achieved by other mechanisms which enhance the opportunities for tenants an</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">d communitie</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">s to shape how land </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">is managed. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">3.2 </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">In this respect</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> the</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> Committee’s</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">briefing </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">paper</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> largely confines </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">consideration of </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">land reform to the transfer of ownership. While there may be merits to this in many cases</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> it is equally true that many tenant farmers d</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">o not find ownership attractive. Indeed, the STFA survey referred to in the report states </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">that </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">80% of respondents believed rural communities would benefit from ‘greater diversity of ownership’ rather than simply land transfer. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">3.3 </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">The Crown Estate works </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">in close partnership with communities (through development trusts, liaison groups etc.</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">,) in a way that empowers them </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">without them having to take on the liabilities</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">associated with ownership. The </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Scotland’s</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> Rural College </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">makes this point i</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">n their respons</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">e </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">to the Scottish Government’s Land Reform R</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">eview</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> Group</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">:</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">3.4 </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">"While there are many examples of successful community landowners in the Highlands and Islands, </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">it is not a panacea and success is never easy, requiring a great deal of</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic"> sustained effort by all sta</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">keholders. There are instances where close partnership working between landowners and rural </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">communities brings significant mutual benefits, and avoids the responsibilities and costs for communities of owning the land."</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">3.5 </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">This is echoed in a report for </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">the Big Lottery, Growing Community Assets Evaluation (Final Year Report).</span><a name="_ftnref4"></a><a href="#_ftn4">[4]</a><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> SCDI, in their response </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">to</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> the Scottish </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Government’s</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> Land R</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">e</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">f</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">orm Re</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">view Group, </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">indicate the relative importance of factors other than land </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">ownership</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">:</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">3.6 </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">“</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">SCDI understands that, </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">in some cases, ownership of land is a central factor in economic growth, particularly where an owner is a barrier to development or fails to maintain their land holding. SCDI recognises the benefits that community ownership can have on fragile communities </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">as has been demonstrated with both </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">Gigha</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic"> and </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">Eigg</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">. However; in most cases the ownership of land is secondary to the impact of factors such as the economic climate, government legislative measures, taxation or other policy leavers, and the lack of discussio</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">n over land use</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">.”</span><a name="_ftnref5"></a><a href="#_ftn5">[5]</a></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">3.7 </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">For this reason</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> it will be just as important to ensure that estates pursue good practice i</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">n terms of both integrated land-use and </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">giving tenants and communities a stake in their </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">land</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">, within the broader context of sustainable economi</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">c development</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">.</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">4. </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Our work with rural &amp; coastal communities</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">4.1 </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">From the perspective of The Crown Estate, there are three strands of our work which </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">relate to issues raised in the Committee’s briefing paper.</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> These include:</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Enabling communities and indiv</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">iduals to maximise their stake in the management of local assets</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Helping communities, particularly those in rural and coastal areas, to become stronger and more resilient</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Investing expertise and capital in order to generate, support, promote and deliver ne</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">w relationships between land, people, economy and environment</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">4.2 </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">We would suggest that some of the ways in which we</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">enable tenants and communities to manage land and foreshore across </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">our </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">rural and coastal estates may offer models for other landowners. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">4.3 </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">These range from structuring leases to meet the stated desire of a community for direct management and control, supporting locally-run organisations to manage assets, a</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">nd our </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Local Management Agreements</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> an </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">initiative</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">introduced in 2012 following the C</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">ommittee’s</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> inquiry into The Crown Estate. LMAs</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> empower communities to manage areas of the foreshore.</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Below we provide examples and </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">outline</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> the benefits that these initiatives have delivered. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">4.4 </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Local Management Agreements (LMA</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">s</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">)</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">LMAs were introduced as </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">pilots by The Crown Estate in 2012 in response to request</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">s</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> by some </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">ports and harbours</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> to have a degree of certainty over use of </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">foreshore and seabed</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> for future developments. In </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">addressing</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> this issue we have widened the scope to be more inclusive and delive</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">r benefits for the wider</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> coastal and marine community.</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">LMAs are designed to enable organisations to develop proposals for areas of foresho</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">re and seabed </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">to </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">deliver</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> benefits to the local community</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">. </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">They provide certainty that a lease can be secured, once proposals and consents are in place – this early-stage certainty in turn enables projects to secure initial </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">investment,</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> for example, </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">to fund </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">feasibility studies</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> and pre-planning work</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">.</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">The first </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">pilots are</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> as follows:</span></li></ul><ul type="circle" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Courier New'; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 47.6pt; padding-left:6.4pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Comann</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">-</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">na</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">-</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Mara </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">on North </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Uist</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> where the</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">agreement </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">will</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">pave the way for floating pontoons with 26 ber</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">ths,</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> a car park and a boat park. T</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">he Crown Estate is investing £38</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">0,000 in the project.</span></li><li style="font-family:'Courier New'; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 47.6pt; padding-left:6.4pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Po</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">r</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">tree</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">where </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">planned </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">improvements </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">for</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> the ha</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">rbour</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> include the installation of a breakwater to enable more cruise ships to stop (bringing significant economic benefits to the island) and an improved slipway which will result in a reduced response time for the RNLI. We have co-funded feasibility studi</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">es  to help progress the plan</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">s</span></li><li style="font-family:'Courier New'; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 47.6pt; padding-left:6.4pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Gigha</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> where the </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">LMA will allow the Isle of </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Gigha</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> Heritage Trust to develop its plans for the area, following a recent grant of £270,925 from the Coastal Communities Fund.</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">The LMA will provide the means for a lease for</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> the walkway and pontoon at </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Ardminish</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> Bay; and to</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> agree a revised mooring area for the Trust’s visitor moorings with room for expansion </span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">4.5 </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">We </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">are seeking</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> further LMA proposals from communities in Scotland and other parts of the UK</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">, and have been working</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> to raise awareness through media, our own publications and website, and through relevant member organisations such as Development Trust Association Scotland.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">4.6 </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Our programme of LMA publicity includes:</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 46.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Media coverage in a range of national, regional an</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">d local outlets </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">focussed on the launch of LMAs in May 2012 followed by the launch </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">of the pilots in February 2013. </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">These two launches were attended by Gareth Baird, Scottish Commissioner, and Alison </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Nimmo</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">, Chief Executive, respectively</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">.</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 46.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Two e-newsletters, e</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">ach di</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">stributed to approximately 250</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Scottish </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">political </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">stakeholders; f</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">eatures in two editions of our Scotland Bulletin publication, distributed to 2000</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">NGOs, tenants, MSPs, councillors etc </span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 46.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">We have appealed to members of the Rural Affairs, Climate Change </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">and Environment Committee</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">in the Scottish Parliament</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> and other MSPs </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">to raise awareness among their constituents</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 46.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">A comprehensive brochure and a</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> new community toolkit. T</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">he latter covers a range of </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">mechanisms</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> (LMAs, the Marine Stewardship Fund, moorings) </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">that</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">enable the </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">public and communities to access our support and resources</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 46.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Liaised with Development Trusts Association Scotland</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">, </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">CoSLA</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> and</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> Community Land Scotland to ensure their members are aware of LMAs and </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">how they may help</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> their </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">community organisations to</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">realise </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">their aspirations</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 46.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Highlighting LMAs in speeches, meetings with stakeholders and other opportunities as they arise</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 46.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">On-going day-to-day promotion by our managing agents and moorings officers</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">4.7 </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">LMAs</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> can be customised to meet the needs/aspirations of</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> individual communities. The projects should be led and driven by local organisations, and have broad buy-in from the community. This will help ensure that they are sustainable in the long-term and that they result in genuine devolution of the management o</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">f assets.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">4.8 </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Local management of moorings</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">We established the Clyde Moorings Committee,</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> a voluntary body, whose members</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> oversee boat mooring applications in the </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Clydeport</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> Harbour Authority area. The Committee is an excellent example of collaborative working within the marine community</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">.</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">We have enco</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">uraged and facilitated over 50 mooring a</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">ssociations around Scotland, giving </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">coastal communities greater management over their local waters</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">.</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">4.9 </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Community liaison </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">We set up the </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Tomintoul</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> and </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Glenlivet</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> Community Liaison Group in 2004. The Group meets twice-yearly with the remit of identifying opportunities for community engagement</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> in estate management activities.</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">This builds on a close working relationship which has been developed over 25 years with the local community on the </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Glenlivet</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> Estate through its locally-based ranger service and managing agents.</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">This approach has helped del</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">iver:</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="circle" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Courier New'; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 65.6pt; padding-left:6.4pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">The £6</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">00,000 </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Glenlivet</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> mountain biking trails and centre</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> (with £375,00 fro</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">m The Crown Estate)</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">, which will </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">open </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">this autumn</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> </span></li><li style="font-family:'Courier New'; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 65.6pt; padding-left:6.4pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Development of three new business units </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">for</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> local business</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">es, creating opportunities </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> for </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">local </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">economic growth </span></li><li style="font-family:'Courier New'; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 65.6pt; padding-left:6.4pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Six miles of </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">community paths and 1</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">00 miles of </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">waymarked</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> footpaths</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">built and maintained</span></li><li style="font-family:'Courier New'; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 65.6pt; padding-left:6.4pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Collaborative</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> working on community and economic regeneration</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> including funding</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> tourism literature, direct advertising and joint promotional activities. </span></li><li style="font-family:'Courier New'; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 65.6pt; padding-left:6.4pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Development and provision of </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">educational services and facilities for schools, visiting groups and higher education institutions to participate in land-based learning, helping to promote knowledge and understanding of rural land use management</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">4.10 </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Working with development trusts</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">4.1</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">1 </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">We are partner in this project (alongside HIE, CNPA and Moray</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> Council)</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">, which </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">has set up </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">the </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Tomintoul</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> and </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Glen</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">livet</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> Development Trust.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">4.12 </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Both the Project and the Trust</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">aim</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> to grow the local econ</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">omy and build the </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">resilience of the community, through </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">locally-driven initiatives.</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> This in turn will increase the </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">community’s stake in the management and development of land and land assets</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">4.13 </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">In addition, we </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">are </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">work</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">ing</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> closely with </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">the </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Rosewell</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> Development Trust to help them achieve develop a community </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">hub in the village</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> and recently established at LMA with the Isle of </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Gigha</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> Heritage Trust</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">. </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">4.14 </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Encouraging new entrants and supporting agricultural businesses</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 27.91pt; padding-left:7.79pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">W</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">e have applied our expertise in farming business to improve the configuration and viability o</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">f farms to maximise the</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">ir </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">economic potential </span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 27.91pt; padding-left:7.79pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">This helps to attract </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">new entran</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">ts and also encourages  next generation farmers</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 27.91pt; padding-left:7.79pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">We support next generation farmers in various ways – through supporting secession, agreeing long term leases, and an on-going programme of investment in units which ensures that they are fit-for purpose </span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 27.91pt; padding-left:7.79pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">We were one of the first landowners in Scotland to a</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">dopt the new form of Limited Duration tenancy in the Agricultural Holdings (Scotland) 2003 Act and promote full farming units on the open market, allowing the next generation of young farmers to emerge and s</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">ecure the future of this vital </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">sector</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">.</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 27.91pt; padding-left:7.79pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">In the las</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">t five years we have put a total of eight units on the</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> open market. This has resulted</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">in five new entrants and three next generation tenants taking on Limited Duration tenancies.</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 27.91pt; padding-left:7.79pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">We are </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">working</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> with tenants on micro and small-scale renewable energy</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> projects</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> and have</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> already invested, as a JV partner</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> with a tenant farmer, in </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">installing PV solar panels at a</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">farm</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> at </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Fochabers</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">. This will help to insulate the farmer from volatile energy prices</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">. </span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">5. </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Further detail on activity since the Scottish Affairs Committee Inquiry into The Crown Estate</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">5.1 </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">The briefing paper references progress (or lack of) following the Committee’s inquiry into The Crown Estate. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">5.2 </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">On request of the Committee, we recently submitted written evidence outlining how we have responded to the Inquiry, the report of which was published in March 2012. This is included in Appendix 1 and details progress in a range of areas such as stakeholder engagement, accountability and transparency, and how or activity generates benefits for communities.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">6. Conclusion</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">6.1 We believe that our approach to working with both rural and coastal communities reflects good practice in a way that does not necessarily rely on the transfer of land. This includes:</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Our commitment to working with partners at a local and national level to maximise the tangible and lasting benefits to communities, individual and other stakeholders</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Our approach to working with tenants, in particular our drive to devolve day-to-day management of land and foreshore (where appropriate)</span></li></ul><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Our activity to engage with, enable and empower communities</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Appendix 1</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Update from The Crown Estate to the Scottish Affairs Committee</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Introduction</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">We welcome the opportunity to update the Committee on the progress made in response to the conclusions and recommendations of your inquiry into The Crown Estate, the report of which was published on 19 March 2012. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Some of the recommendations are matters for Government rather than The Crown Estate, including the recommendation on devolution of The Crown Estate. The UK Government responded to the Scottish Affairs Committee’s (SAC) Report in July 2012.  </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">This response outlines how we have worked to address the general conclusions in the Report and the specific recommendations that were accepted by the UK Government as actions for The Crown Estate.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">The Crown Estate in Scotland</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">The Crown Estate is committed to Scotland. Our annual reports illustrate how we are building and strengthening relations with stakeholders, and how we leverage expertise and investment from our UK-wide business to support key sectors in Scotland.</span><a name="_ftnref6"></a><a href="#_ftn6">[6]</a></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Our remit is to maintain and enhance the value of our assets over the long-term while delivering a return to government, and to do so with due regard to good management. This means that, in managing assets commercially, we consider how our investments and developments may deliver real benefits to communities, to Scotland and to the UK generally.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">In fulfilling this role, our team in Scotland and London work to enable and facilitate sustainable economic development.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">In mature sectors, such as tourism and aquaculture, we invest in, and secure investment in, specific projects (e.g. marine leisure developments). We also work with industry, local authorities and agencies such as Highlands &amp; Islands Enterprise (HIE), to ensure a coordinated and collaborative approach at local, regional and national level.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">In emerging sectors such as offshore </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">renewables</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> and carbon capture &amp; storage (CCS), we coordinate a range of strategic activity designed to accelerate development and de-risk investment. We work closely with organisations such as Marine Scotland, Scottish Enterprise and local authorities, in addition to developers and energy companies, to help establish this sector within the UK’s energy mix.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Activity since the SAC Report</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">We have identified below the general categories within the conclusions and recommendations section of the SAC’s Report on The Crown Estate. In each case we have identified the actions undertaken by The Crown Estate in response. We have also indicated where a recommendation is outside of our remit, as defined in The Crown Estate Act 1961.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><ol type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 31.25pt; padding-left:4.75pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Accountability</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">The current arrangements in respect of formal accountability to the Treasury and the Scotland Office are defined within the 1961 Crown Estate Act.  It would require primary legislation to change this.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">In its response to the Committee’s report, the Government acknowledged the measures being undertaken by The Crown Estate to improve accountability. These include offering to give oral evidence annually to the Scottish Parliament’s Rural Affairs, Climate Change &amp; Environment Committee and the Economy, Energy &amp; Tourism Committee to provide MSPs the opportunity to scrutinise the work of The Crown Estate in Scotland. The Crown Estate attended the Rural Affairs, Climate Change and Environment Committee on 14 November 2012 and 11 September 2013 and the Economy, Energy and Tourism Committee on 27 March 2013.</span><a name="_ftnref7"></a><a href="#_ftn7">[7]</a><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">The Government also set up an Inter-Ministerial Strategic Group (IMSG), chaired by a Treasury Minister, with membership from The Crown Estate, the Scotland Office and the Scottish Government, as well as a local authority representative. The Group will consider the activities of The Crown Estate and review its strategy for the year ahead.  The first meeting of the Group is scheduled to take place on 6 November.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">The officials’ group set up to support the IMSG met in February 2013 and agreed terms of reference and a standing agenda. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="2" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 31.25pt; padding-left:4.75pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Finance</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">The Crown Estate is a UK-wide organisation with an award-winning approach to integrated reporting.</span><a name="_ftnref8"></a><a href="#_ftn8">[8]</a><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> In line with standard practice, we do not provide net accounts for Scotland. However, we</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic"> </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">have provided some information about gross expenditure in our Scotland Report derived from our NAO audited accounts. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">This information has included disaggregating the Scottish component of our investment in the Round 3 offshore wind programme (two of the nine Round 3 projects are in Scottish waters), in response to a request from the Rural Affairs, Climate Change &amp; Environment Committee. This investment has primarily been in our Enabling Actions, a programme of strategic activity designed to de-risk investment and accelerate development.  </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="3" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 31.25pt; padding-left:4.75pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Communications and engagement</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">The Crown Estate now has an extensive and structured programme of regular stakeholder engagement which includes Government, parliamentarians, local authorities, government agencies, NDPBs, commercial and community partners, along with industry representative bodies. For example, there is now a schedule of meetings with Scottish Ministers in addition to the regular Scottish Parliament Committee sessions.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">The Crown Estate set up the Scottish Liaison Group in 2007 comprising key stakeholders, this Group has been supplemented with separate meetings for particular sectors such as offshore renewable energy and aquaculture. By developing the format in this way, we aim to improve co-ordination, sharing of information and ensure the Group is working to best effect. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">In addition, we hold annual receptions in Edinburgh and a range of workshops with stakeholders (such as the one held with senior team of HIE and our Chief Executive in September 2013). We have established a Memorandum of Understanding with the University of Highlands &amp; Islands, </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">to help communities benefit from the generation of low carbon energy</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">, focusing on creating the right training infrastructure and in promoting innovation and research.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">We also contribute to wider debates, providing our insight and expertise to help inform policy debate and decision-making. We responded to the Scottish Government-commissioned Land Reform Review Group’s consultation in January 2013. In addition, our Chief Executive, Scottish Commissioner and Rural and Coastal Portfolio Manager for Scotland met with members of the Group including the Chair, Dr Alison Eliot, in September 2013. We intend to respond to the Scottish Affairs Committee’s consultation on land reform.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">We are partners in a range of joint-working initiatives, reflecting our commitment to working collaboratively with stakeholders at the local, regional and national level.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">The managing agents’ contract for the coastal estate has been retendered to ensure that they are more firmly embedded within the communities that they serve and we are rolling out engagement training for all managing agents.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="4" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 31.25pt; padding-left:4.75pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Community benefits and wider public interests</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">We work closely with communities to meet shared objectives. While The Crown Estate Act 1961 does constrain the organisation’s capacity to invest in projects that do not meet its commercial remit, in practice the overall programme of investment is aligned with supporting sustainable economic growth in Scotland. On this basis, communities do benefit from reinvestment of revenues raised.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">In response to concerns raised by coastal communities, we introduced Local Management Agreements (LMAs) in 2012. LMAs provide access to seabed and foreshore and help local communities to secure funds to develop projects designed to take advantage of the economic opportunities offered by, for example, the growth of marine leisure.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Three such agreements now exist for proposed projects in </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Lochmaddy</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">, </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Portree</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> and </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Gigha</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">. Our team provides on-going support and advice to the project partners, and we recently announced a £380,000 investment in </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Coman</span><a name="_GoBack"></a><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">n</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">na</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> Mara’s development at </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Lochmaddy</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">, North </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Uist</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">We are also investing £375,000 in new mountain bike facilities on the </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Glenlivet</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> Estate, including new bike trails and a visitor centre. This builds on our work in recent decades to develop the area as a tourist destination, supporting business diversification and community regeneration. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">In relation to offshore renewable energy, we are piloting an education programme for secondary pupils (working with </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Keir</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> Bloomer’s team at the Sustainable Learning Partnership) to ensure that they are aware of and able to take advantage of opportunities in offshore </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">renewables</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">. The programme is project-based, cross-curricular and is aligned with Curriculum for Excellence, using active learning to cover wider themes of sustainability.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Last year The Crown Estate invested £9.6 million in Scotland of which £5.9 million was in the Energy &amp; Infrastructure portfolio covering offshore </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">renewables</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> and carbon capture &amp; storage (CCS). In addition, around £100,000 is invested each year in coastal projects through the Marine Stewardship Fund and £200,000 is invested in aquaculture research (this will rise to £250,000 per year from 2013/14).</span><a name="_ftnref9"></a><a href="#_ftn9">[9]</a><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Much of our work is designed to unlock potential. A recent example is our work with Scottish Government and HIE to facilitate BT’s </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">installation of 400km of subsea cables over 19 crossings to islands to deliver fibre broadband to over 80% homes and businesses in Highlands &amp; Islands. </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Recognising the significant social and economic benefits that broadband will bring communities, The Crown Estate made a variation to standard terms for submarine telecoms cables. This helped make the project viable and gave BT certainty at an early stage. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">A further example is our work on data-sharing designed to help further sector development by addressing knowledge gaps and avoiding duplication of surveys or other forms of research. Our bespoke spatial planning tool </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">MaRS</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> has been used by Marine Scotland to help inform marine planning, and the Marine Data Exchange (found at http://www.marinedataexchange.co.uk/) provides </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">access to survey data and reports collated during the planning, building and operating of offshore renewable energy projects.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="5" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 31.25pt; padding-left:4.75pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Two phase decentralisation, transition, foreshore and seabed rights</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">These changes would require primary legislation</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">However, at an operational level The Crown Estate has agreed in principle appropriate protocols with Marine Scotland to ensure that our energy activities, roles and responsibilities, are aligned with the objectives of Scottish Government. Equally, we work closely with local authorities, particularly those in the Highlands &amp; Islands, to ensure effective collaboration and cooperation.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="6" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 31.25pt; padding-left:4.75pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Historic sites</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">The SAC’s objectives have been met in full. The Crown Estate transferred the land in West Princes Street Gardens to the City of Edinburgh Council in October 2012. In August 2013, King’s Park was transferred to Scottish Ministers, while ensuring local control and management of the land through a ground lease to Stirling Council.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="7" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 31.25pt; padding-left:4.75pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Ancient rights</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">The transfer of naturally occurring oysters and mussels to Marine Scotland on behalf of Scottish Ministers has been agreed in principle and is expected to be completed in the next few months. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">The commercial value of salmon, gold and silver prevent the transfer of these at nil value due to the requirements of The Crown Estate Act.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">There are close to 140 river salmon fishing tenancies, including more than a third with angling clubs or associations</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">. We</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> seek to encourage other such groups to take up leases and have recently supported new local angling associations by granting leases on the River Leven in Fife and the West Lothian Almond, enabling the communities to enjoy access to salmon angling at an affordable cost (reflecting the recovering salmon stocks and water quality). </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="8" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 31.25pt; padding-left:4.75pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Modern acquisitions</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">The Crown Estate continues to buy and sell land and property on this basis.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">We welcome the continued interest and engagement of the Scottish Affairs Committee members in our work and, for our part, would be keen to continue this dialogue and to arrange site visits to areas where we are active.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">October 2013</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p></div><hr style="width:33%; height:1px; text-align:left" /><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn1"></a><a href="#_ftnref1">[1]</a><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt"> The response is available here </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt">http://www.thecrownestate.co.uk/about-us/scotland/</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn2"></a><a href="#_ftnref2">[2]</a><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt">The Government response is here </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt">http://www.official-documents.gov.uk/document/cm83/8361/8361.pdf</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt"> </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn3"></a><a href="#_ftnref3">[3]</a><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt">The 2012/13 Scotland Report </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt">can be found here </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10.5pt">http://www.thecrow</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10.5pt">nestate.co.uk/media/422027/scotland-report-2013.pdf</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn4"></a><a href="#_ftnref4">[4]</a><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt"> See paragraphs 2.26 and 14.22 in the report found at </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt">http://www.biglotteryfund.org.uk/r</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt">esearch/stronger-communities/evaluating-growing-community-assets</span></p><p style="font-size:10pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><a name="_ftn5"></a><a href="#_ftnref5">[5]</a><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt"> See </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt">http://www.scdi.org.uk/pi/2013/SCDI_response_to_the_Land_Reform_Review_Group.pdf</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt"> </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn6"></a><a href="#_ftnref6">[6]</a><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt">The 2012/13 Scotland Report </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt">can be found here </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10.5pt">http://www.thecrownestate.co.uk/media/422027/scotland-report-2013.pdf</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn7"></a><a href="#_ftnref7">[7]</a><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:9pt"> We have also taken part in two Rural Affairs Committee roundtables in recent months, one focussed on aquaculture and one on marine planning.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn8"></a><a href="#_ftnref8">[8]</a><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:9pt"> In October 2013 we won the public sector category award in PWC’s</span><span style="color:#5c5c5c; font-family:Calibri; font-size:9pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:9pt">Building Public Trust Awards for our progress towards integrated reporting.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn9"></a><a href="#_ftnref9">[9]</a><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:9pt"> This is separate from and in addition to the Coastal Communities Fund (CCF). The CCF was set up by HM Treasury and is administered by the Big Lottery Fund. It consists of 50 per cent of the annual gross revenues from The Crown Estate’s marine activities. From 2012/13 to 2015/16, this will total £10.85 million. CCF is aimed at projects that promote sustainable economic development.</span></p></body></html>